.\docs\setup\wave-2-implementation-runbook.md:17:`prove-features-gate.ps1` reads `policies/proof-policy.yaml`, verifies receipts via cosign/ed25519, and computes/verifies bundle merkle roots. Exits 1 on any policy violation. `-ExternalJudge` becomes default; `-Local` is loud opt-in.
.\docs\setup\wave-2-implementation-runbook.md:40:A new workflow `proof-gate.yml` runs `prove-features-gate.ps1` against the latest bundle on every PR. Required check for merge to main.
.\docs\setup\wave-2-implementation-runbook.md:73:| 4.6 | Bundle aggregator collects bridge_receipts and includes them in merkle root | `proof_signing.py` aggregator path; bundle schema update |
.\docs\setup\wave-2-implementation-runbook.md:77:- Proof bundle includes a list of `bridge_receipts` that the gate verifies match the recorded session.
.\docs\setup\wave-2-implementation-runbook.md:88:| Phase 4 independent of Phases 2-3 | Bridge HMAC ships and is consumed by the bundle aggregator regardless of CI status |
.\docs\setup\wave-2-implementation-runbook.md:96:| #194 | closed | UI registry wiring lets us produce more meaningful proof bundles |
.\docs\setup\wave-2-implementation-runbook.md:97:| #166 | closed | Path-injection fix is the precondition for trusting bundle paths |
.\docs\setup\wave-1-acceptance-runbook.md:167:Wave 2 (smart-contract proof system, signed receipts, merkle bundle) builds on this foundation.
.\docs\setup\first-external-receipt-runbook.md:9:1. **MOONSHOT_API_KEY** — get one at <https://platform.moonshot.cn/console/api-keys>. The free tier is enough for proof bundles.
.\docs\setup\first-external-receipt-runbook.md:32:Pick something in the game window that's tied to a feature you want to verify — a HUD element after a stat override, a Star Wars unit visual after the AssetSwap fix, a menu after pack hot-reload, etc.
.\docs\setup\first-external-receipt-runbook.md:74:- **`disputed: true`** — external Kimi judge disagrees with local CLIP tier. This is a feature, not a bug. Do not promote the bundle. Investigate the actual screenshot.
.\docs\setup\first-external-receipt-runbook.md:78:Every `prove-features` bundle before this runbook ran was Claude grading Claude. After this lands, DINOForge has at least one feature with verifiable, replayable, external-judged proof on disk. That's the artifact "verified" claims are supposed to point at.
