.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:1:# AssetSwapSystem Truth Audit — 2026-04-24
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:5:The AssetSwapSystem is working code that has never been observed working in production because the input data it consumes is mismatched and the unit-test surface that "validates" it uses substitute `FakeAssetBundle` / `FakeSwappableEntity` types instead of real bundles.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:12:- `AssetSwapSystem.ApplySwap` (lines 165–224): real — calls `assetService.ExtractAsset()`, `assetService.ReplaceAsset()`, writes patched bundles to `BepInEx/dinoforge_patched_bundles/`.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:13:- `AssetSwapSystem.TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` (lines 233–418): real — loads bundles, extracts `Mesh` / `Material` from prefab, mutates ECS entity `RenderMesh` shared component via reflection (`meshField.SetValue()` at line 374, `materialField.SetValue()` at line 387).
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:15:### AssetSwapRegistry population — REAL but conditional
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:16:- `ContentLoader.RegisterAssetSwaps` (lines 295–334): iterates `RegistryManager.Units.All`, registers entries with `visual_asset` field.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:17:- Gates on `File.Exists(bundlePath)` (line 309) — registry is empty when bundles aren't built. (Star Wars pack ships 18 real bundles + 12 stub bundles per prior audit; the 18 do pass this gate.)
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:22:- Fallback (lines 95–107): if parse fails, assigns all assets to first bundle — heuristic, not guaranteed correct.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:25:### Smoking gun: bundle asset names do not match `visual_asset`
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:27:`AssetSwapTests.cs` lines 28–29 (verbatim, in source):
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:29:> Root cause of the current 0/36 swap failure: bundle names don't match the visual_asset YAML field.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:31:`AssetSwapTests.cs` line 99 (verbatim):
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:36:1. ✅ `ContentLoader.RegisterAssetSwaps` runs, registers 36 entries in `AssetSwapRegistry`.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:37:2. ✅ `AssetSwapSystem.OnUpdate` waits 600 frames, calls `ApplySwap`.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:39:4. ✅ Calls `bundle.LoadAsset<Mesh>("sw-clone-trooper")` (the `visual_asset` key).
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:40:5. ❌ Returns null — the bundle contains a mesh named `CloneTrooperMesh` (or whatever the FBX asset name was), not `sw-clone-trooper`.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:41:6. ❌ Falls back to `bundle.LoadAsset<GameObject>` — also returns null.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:42:7. ❌ Logs "no Mesh/Material named X in bundle" and returns false.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:50:`src/Tests/Integration/Tests/AssetSwapTests.cs` and adjacent fixtures use:
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:51:- `FakeAssetBundle` — substitute that returns the requested asset by name regardless of bundle contents.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:52:- `FakeAssetSwapSystem` — substitute that records swap calls without actually loading bundles.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:55:These tests pass at green every CI run. They confirm the *control flow* of swap calls. They do not exercise the *data path* (bundle name vs `visual_asset` key match) where the real failure lives.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:57:`TRACEABILITY_VERIFICATION_20260420.md` cites tests like `AssetSwapTests.EntitySwap_ReplacesVanillaWithCustom` as evidence of asset-swap "verified." Those tests exclusively use the Fake* types.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:63:1. **Data layer**: either rename each `visual_asset` key in pack YAML to match the real asset name inside the corresponding bundle (manual sync), OR change `TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` to use `bundle.LoadAllAssets()` and find by type rather than by name (already a fallback at lines around 280, but not the first try). The right fix is probably "iterate `LoadAllAssets`, pick first `Mesh`/`Material`" rather than name-keyed lookup, since bundle names are an Addressables internal detail Pack authors shouldn't need to know.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:65:2. **Test layer**: replace `FakeAssetBundle` etc. with a real-bundle integration test using one of the 18 real Star Wars bundles. If the test can't run on Linux CI (Unity bundle loading needs Windows + DirectX adapters), gate it behind a `WINDOWS_GAME_AVAILABLE` env var and explicitly fail CI when that variable isn't set on the machine running asset-swap-related changes — rather than silently skipping.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:67:3. **Telemetry**: when `AssetSwapSystem` fails a swap, the failure should surface in `dinoforge_debug.log` AND in the `game_status` MCP tool's response, so an agent doing `prove-features` can detect "we shipped 18 bundles and 0 of them ever rendered" without having to read source code.
.\docs\sessions\daily\2026-04-24\2026-04-24-asset-swap-truth-audit.md:71:| AssetSwapSystem (in-game render of mod bundles) | ❌ STUB (functional code, broken data path) | Implementation real (loads bundles, mutates ECS entities). 0 of 36 Star Wars unit swaps render at runtime because `visual_asset` YAML key doesn't match the asset name inside the bundle. Tests pass because they use `FakeAssetBundle`. Fix: change lookup from name-keyed to type-keyed `LoadAllAssets()` first-match, and replace fake tests with real-bundle integration tests. |
