.\docs\adr\ADR-002-declarative-first-architecture.md:34:- Agents mostly author YAML/JSON manifests and content bundles
.\docs\asset-intake\assetctl-prd.md:69:- `assetctl export-unity <asset_id> [--bundle unit|vehicle|prop]`
.\docs\asset-pipeline-governance.md:75:Asset bundles for DINO **must be built with Unity 2021.3.45f2**. Bundles from other versions fail to load silently at runtime.
.\docs\asset-pipeline-governance.md:83:5. → packs/<pack-id>/assets/bundles/<asset-id>   (bundle file)
.\docs\asset-pipeline-governance.md:89:- Bundle filename = `visual_asset` key = Addressable key used by AssetSwapRegistry
.\docs\asset-pipeline-governance.md:90:- Example: `sw-rep-clone-trooper` for file `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/bundles/sw-rep-clone-trooper`
.\docs\asset-pipeline-governance.md:91:- The asset name **inside** the bundle is the Unity prefab name (e.g. `sw-rep-clone-trooper.prefab`)
.\docs\asset-pipeline-governance.md:92:- AssetSwapSystem uses `bundle.LoadAllAssets()` fallback to handle name mismatches
.\docs\ASSET_CLI_IMPLEMENTATION.md:20:### Bundle Inspection Commands (Legacy, under `bundles`)
.\docs\ASSET_CLI_IMPLEMENTATION.md:22:Moved legacy bundle inspection commands to separate `bundles` command group for clarity:
