.\docs\design\2026-04-25-smart-contract-proof-system.md:255:5. At bundle-finalize time, the aggregated `BridgeReceipt` records (one per call) are concatenated, hashed, and that aggregate hash is what gets cosign-signed inside the BundleManifest.
.\docs\design\2026-04-25-smart-contract-proof-system.md:263:Every BundleManifest carries `previous_bundle_hash`. Construction:
.\docs\design\2026-04-25-smart-contract-proof-system.md:265:- `previous_bundle_hash = sha256(prior_manifest.json_bytes_with_signature)`.
.\docs\design\2026-04-25-smart-contract-proof-system.md:266:- The first bundle (genesis) sets `previous_bundle_hash = null` and is committed to git as the chain root.
.\docs\design\2026-04-25-smart-contract-proof-system.md:267:- Tampering with bundle N flips its sha256, which breaks bundle N+1's chain.
.\docs\design\2026-04-25-smart-contract-proof-system.md:269:The git commit history of `docs/proof/bundles/` becomes a second-axis verifier: bundle hashes baked into the git log give a third witness (Sigstore + ed25519 + git).
