.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:149:**Short answer: No — not for functional Unity-runtime bundles.**
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:151:AssetsTools.NET (used by `DINOForge.SDK.Assets.AssetService` for catalog reading and bundle patching) can:
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:153:- Read `Mesh` type data (vertices, indices) and write it back to an existing bundle slot
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:157:- Serialize a `Mesh` asset in the Unity binary format that `AssetBundle.LoadAsset<Mesh>()` can deserialize — this requires the Unity type tree, which varies per Unity version and is embedded in bundles built by that version's `BuildPipeline`
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:160:Attempting to write a raw `Mesh` binary into an AssetsTools bundle file would produce a file that passes `AssetBundle.LoadFromFile()` (the header is valid) but causes `LoadAsset<Mesh>()` to either return null or throw a `UnityException` — the same symptom as the 90-byte stubs.
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:162:**Therefore**: Unity 2021.3.45f1 batchmode is the required and only viable path for producing loadable bundles.
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:164:**One narrow exception**: If a bundle was already built by Unity 2021.3 (e.g. the 44KB primitive bundles), AssetsTools.NET *could* in principle overwrite the Mesh bytes with new geometry in-place, since the type tree is already correct for this Unity version. This would be a "bundle patch" approach — copy a working primitive bundle and replace its mesh data. This is feasible for swapping geometry but is fragile (requires exact size matching or raw binary surgery) and would not give a clean solution. It is not recommended.
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:208:These work (AssetSwap can load and render them) but show Unity primitive geometry, not Star Wars models.
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:212:Of these, **many have FBX source files** in `unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Models/` and `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/source/` that were never promoted to real bundles:
.\docs\qa\assetswap-real-bundles-spec.md:218:| `sw-rep-clone-engineer` | `rep_clone_engineer.fbx` (560 KB) — YES (already has real bundle) |
